<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="10Mar1939"><font color="red">10 March 1939</font> <i>NLFF</i> (from Richard de la Mere to Paul L&eacute;on): We shall be able to bring the book out on May 4th &hellip; necessity of using gold for the lettering &hellip; But Mr Joyce&apos;s plan for the contrasting yellow can be kept by colouring the top edges of the book with the yellow that I used on the previous specimen for the lettering &hellip; I am also carrying out his colour scheme on the jacket of the ordinary edition. </div>
